librelp
------------------------------------------
librelp is an easy to use library for the RELP protocol. RELP in turn provides
reliable event logging over the network (and consequently RELP stands for
Reliable Event Logging Protocol). RELP was initiated by Rainer Gerhards after
he was finally upset by the lossy nature of plain tcp syslog and wanted a cure
for all these dangling issues.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.5.4-1
  libgnutls30-3.8.6-1
  librelp-devel-1.11.0-1bl2
  librelp0-1.11.0-1bl2
  libssl3-3.0.15-1
  pkg-config-2.3.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  autoconf-archive-2023.02.20-1
  automake-20240607-1
  binutils-2.43.1-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  libgnutls-devel-3.8.6-1
  libssl-devel-3.0.15-1
  libtool-2.4.7-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/rsyslog/librelp

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/rsyslog/librelp/archive/refs/tags/v1.11.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack librelp-1.11.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./librelp-1.11.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/librelp-1.11.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/librelp-1.11.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/librelp0-1.11.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/librelp-devel-1.11.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(librelp)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/librelp.README
  /usr/share/doc/librelp/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/librelp/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/librelp/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/librelp/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/librelp/README
  /usr/share/doc/librelp/html/gfdl.html
  /usr/share/doc/librelp/html/relp.html

(librelp0)
  /usr/bin/cygrelp-0.dll

(librelp-devel)
  /usr/include/librelp.h
  /usr/lib/librelp.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/relp.pc

